Robert Bates, 73, has been charged with second-degree manslaughter in the April 2 shooting death of Eric Harris, 44 .
Bates has said he mistakenly pulled out a handgun rather than a stun gun when he fatally shot Harris on April 2 .
On Friday, he apologized to the family of the man he killed and said he 'rate this as number one on my list of things in my life that I regret'